{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"BootStep"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each "},{"code":"BootStep","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" pairs a delay (time to wait before acting) with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an action to perform. The delay accounts for Setup Assistant"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"screen transitions, which vary depending on the macOS version"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and VM performance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"How It Works","anchor":"How-It-Works","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Setup Assistant automation sends keyboard input to the VM’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"virtual display using "},{"code":"VZVirtualMachineView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". This follows the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"same approach used by "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/cirruslabs\/tart"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for Packer "},{"code":"boot_command","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" sequences, which has been proven"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reliable across macOS 13 through 26."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Important","style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"VZVirtualMachineView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" must be attached to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"VM (even offscreen) for keyboard events to be delivered."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Without a view, the Virtualization framework d